(1) At the intersection of Fulton Street and Broadway, showing at the left on Fulton Street, the Jewell warehouse. The intersections are now (1929) known as Jewell Square. Overhead is the terminal for a series of Elevated lines of the B.M.T., junctioning at this point. In the background is Gillen Place.

April 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing the south side of Fulton Street, east of Williams Place. A section of Trinity hospital is also seen. In front of it is displayed an American flag.

April 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
